The '''shellbane gryphon''' is the [[boss]] version of [[gryphon]]s found in a [[Shellbane Gryphon Cave|cave]] in the centre of [[the Great Conch]], requiring level 51 [[Slayer]] and completion of [[Troubled Tortugans]] to kill. As a [[Slayer boss]], it may only be killed while on a gryphons [[Slayer task]]. Gryphon slayer tasks must be unlocked by purchasing the 'Wings Spread' reward from a slayer master for 80 [[Slayer reward point|Slayer Points]] in order to be assigned them by [[Nieve]]/[[Steve]] or [[Duradel]]/[[Kuradal]], though this unlock is not required for the shellbane gryphon to be assigned as a boss task from those slayer masters. [[Konar quo Maten]] can also assign the shellbane gryphon specifically when she assigns a [[boss task]].

The shellbane gryphon can also be killed off-task only if the player has the [[Clue scroll (elite) - Their bane awaits|elite clue step]] to kill the gryphon. Dropping the elite clue scroll while in the cave will delete the item. [[Combat Achievements]] can still be completed when killing the gryphon via this method, though not all are possible due to some requiring several kills without leaving the cave. The gryphon will also not drop anything if the clue is not your inventory when it dies.

[[Elder Nama]] at the cave entrance enforces these rules, and also acts as a [[scoreboard]] for the boss, displaying the player's statistics for the fight as well as global statistics.

The Shellbane gryphon drops the [[Belle's folly (tarnished)|tarnished Belle's folly]], which can be repaired into [[Belle's folly]] with 70 [[Smithing]] at the [[polishing wheel]] inside the [[Giants' Foundry]].

The shellbane gryphon is a solo instanced fight. Once a slayer task has been completed, it will no longer respawn, preventing you from fighting it off-task.

==Location==
The shellbane gryphon is located in a [[Shellbane Gryphon Cave|cave]] in the centre of [[the Great Conch]], north of fairy ring {{Fairycode|CJQ}}.

==Fight overview==
{{Main|Shellbane gryphon/Strategies}}
Like normal gryphons, the shellbane gryphon is primarily weak to [[melee]]. A [[tortugan shield]] is required for the fight, otherwise the player will take heavy damage.

The shellbane gryphon primarily attacks with melee, but also uses a [[ranged]] attack occasionally. It also has three special attacks:
* '''Knockback''' - The boss will throw the player backwards, dealing up to 30 unavoidable damage. It is countered by having the player's '''equipped''' weight be ≥40kg, and then quickly counterattacking when it attempts to use the attack. The boss will prioritise using its other two special attacks if the player weighs ≥40kg. When stun shows above gryphon (orange birds), click on the gryphon to avoid damage.
* '''Corrosive spit''' - An orange blob is launched, which corrodes the player's worn equipment if they do not move one tile away from where they stood. This will deal 3-12 damage 6 times over the course of {{Ticks|32}}. This can be interrupted by quickly unequipping all items. The amount of damage taken from each hitsplat seems to depend on weight and type of worn equipment. {{Fact|Damage dealt appears to differ depending on the type of equipment worn; see talk page for more details.}}
* '''Whirlwind''' -  [[Whirlwind]]s begin to form at the player's current position every {{Ticks|3}}, up to a maximum of 5. These can stack and form a more powerful whirlwind, so it's recommended to move one tile every attack in order to avoid whirlwinds stacking and increasing their size resulting in less damage received. A max stack size 5 whirlwind will hit every square in the room for 50-70+ damage.

